<h2>About the Focus Stage</h2>
<p>The Focus stage consists of finalized drafts produced by the community. This stage acts as a throttle to allow the finalized with the most support to be proposed in front of the legislature by the representative. Each registered voter may only focus on one finalized draft at a time, and the finalized draft with the most support should be proposed next.</p>
<p>Registered voters may discuss and support pieces of legislation. They may also focus on one item at a time.</p>


